{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T03:59:38.696Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"PCA"},{"type":"text","text":" (Principal Component Analysis) is the most widely used "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dimensionality reduction technique"},{"type":"text","text":" that finds the directions where data varies the most and projects it onto those directions — essentially \"rotating the axes\" to align with maximum variance so you can represent high-dimensional data in fewer dimensions without losing much information."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"PCA is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linear feature extraction technique"},{"type":"text","text":" that:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduces dimensions"},{"type":"text","text":": Represents high-dimensional data in fewer dimensions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Preserves variance"},{"type":"text","text":": Keeps the most important structure/information\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Creates new features"},{"type":"text","text":": Principal components are linear combinations of original variables\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Removes redundancy"},{"type":"text","text":": Eliminates correlated features by capturing shared variance"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Intuition"},{"type":"text","text":": Imagine you have a 3D dataset. If you project it onto a 2D plane, you'd like to choose the plane that preserves the most variation. PCA finds exactly that plane."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Two types of dimensionality reduction"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feature Selection"},{"type":"text","text":" → Keep only important original features (e.g., remove low-variance columns)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feature Extraction"},{"type":"text","text":" → Create new features that capture most information (e.g., PCA, t-SNE, UMAP)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"PCA belongs to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"feature extraction"},{"type":"text","text":" (linear dimensionality reduction)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Modern datasets often have "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hundreds or thousands of features"},{"type":"text","text":": pixels in images, gene expressions in biology, words in NLP. This creates challenges:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"PCA Solution"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High computational cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fewer features → faster training"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overfitting"}]}]},{"type":"tab